**THE DAWN OF THE FIRST DAY**, our heroes find themselves at a crossroeads. Each needing to leave their homes to travel deep into a haunted wood, but none willing to do it alone, but with the king's soldiers at their back with swords drawn, chasing them away from the only homes they've ever known, they don't have much of a choice. It's either stay behind and be slain by the kings men, or take their chances in the haunted wood.

**Ingredients:**  1 Can of Coconut Milk 1 Can Cream of Coconut 2 Cans Evaporated Milk 1/2 Cup Sweetened Condensed Milk 1/2 Cup White Rum (Optional) 1 tsp. Vanilla Extract 1/2 tasp. Ground Cinnamon (Can use more for garnish is desired) Cinnamon sticks (optional)  **Instructions:**  1. In bowl of blender, add evaporated milk, cream of coconut, coconut milk, sweetened condensed milk, rum (if using), vanilla extract, and ground cinnamon. Blend on high until mixture is well combined (1-2 minutes).  2. Pour coconut mixture into glass bottles; cover. Transfer to refridgerator. Chill until cold.  3. To serve, stir or shake bottle well to combine. Pour into small serving glasses. Garnish with ground cinnamon and cinnamon sticks, if desired.
